      <h1 class='title'>Equality Commission for Northern Ireland</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 14 July 2004 vol 663 c59WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_59ws' title='Col. 59WS &mdash; HL Deb 14 July 2004 vol 663 c59WS' name='column_59ws' href='#column_59ws' rel='bookmark'>59WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S5LV0663P0_20040714_LWS_1'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-valerie-amos' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0663P0_20040714_LWS_1' title='Link to this speech by Ms Valerie Amos' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-valerie-amos" title="Ms Valerie Amos">The Lord President of the Council (Baroness Amos)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">My right honourable friend the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland has made the following Ministerial Statement.</p><p>Under Section 73(2) of the <a href="/acts/northern-ireland-act-1998">Northern Ireland Act 1998</a>, I have appointed four new commissioners to the Equality Commission for Northern Ireland. They are: Anthony Carlin, Una Gillespie, Thomas McGrath and Paul Yam.</p><p>The appointments take effect from 1 August 2004 and last for three years.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
